# Regional Data Remapping

When API data includes both default and regional fields, keep the raw API data and rebuild displayed data from it whenever language changes.

Applies to fields like:

- `Name` / `Name_Regional`
- `Description` / `Description_Regional`
- `Title` / `Title_Regional`
- `Message` / `Message_Regional`
- lower-case backend variants like `title_Regional`

## Required Pattern

1. Store raw API rows/details unchanged, e.g. `rawEntities`, `rawRoles`, `rawDetails`.
2. Map displayed UI models in a small method, e.g. `mapRawEntities()`.
3. Use `LocalStorageService.getPreferredLanguageCode() === 'ar'` for the current regional state.
4. Subscribe to `LanguageDirService.userLanguageCode$` and re-run the mapping method.
5. Do not reload the API just because language changed, unless the backend returned only one language.

## Avoid

- Do not calculate `isRegional` once inside `load...()` and permanently map `name`, `description`, `title`, or `message`.
- Do not keep only final displayed text when raw regional fields are available.
- Do not let request signature / duplicate-load guards block local remapping.
- Do not remap active edit form inputs while the user may have unsaved changes.

## Example

```ts
private rawEntities: EntityBackend[] = [];

private mapRawEntities(): void {
  const isRegional = this.localStorageService.getPreferredLanguageCode() === 'ar';
  this.entities = this.rawEntities.map((item) => ({
    id: String(item.Entity_ID || ''),
    name: isRegional ? (item.Name_Regional || item.Name || '') : (item.Name || ''),
    description: isRegional ? (item.Description_Regional || item.Description || '') : (item.Description || '')
  }));
}
```
